1783564921553474	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEypBQ		item.create	bn-mq6j	{"description":"From bn-38nz item 2. Design decision (lead): the jj-style model stays — sync COMMITS conflict markers and exits 0 by design (locked in by tests/conflict_state_truth.rs:101-107); do NOT stop-uncommitted like git rebase, do NOT change the exit code (would break && chains for the agents this serves). The fix is loudness only. bn-8zqz already made the summary HONEST; this bone makes it UNMISSABLE.\n\nCHANGES:\n1. sync/rebase.rs:946-961 (new conflicts this run) and :973-988 (residual committed conflicts): prefix the conflict-summary block with \"WARNING:\" like sibling paths already do (rebase.rs:1024-1027, sync/mod.rs:164-168), and duplicate the block to stderr so it survives stdout-swallowing wrappers. Same for the pre-flight variant at sync/mod.rs:140-146.\n2. Sibling auto-rebase line during merge (auto_rebase.rs:83-110 SiblingResult::describe): the conflicted case renders \"rebased with N conflict(s) (...)\" — one terse line blending into the \"rebased clean\" list. Tag it distinctly (e.g. \"CONFLICT: <name> — rebased with N conflict(s); resolve: maw ws resolve <name> --list\").\n3. merge.rs:4483-4510: bubble sibling conflict counts into the merge's own final summary (e.g. \"NOTE: 1 sibling workspace now has conflicts: <name>\"). Today only Failed siblings even get a tracing::warn.\n4. Add --format json to ws sync (sync() at sync/mod.rs:77 has no format param; clap variant workspace/mod.rs:802-820 has no flags). Follow the established format.rs pattern (OutputFormat + hidden --json, used by ws list/merge/diff/status). JSON must include conflict counts + paths so agents can detect committed-conflict state mechanically (this is the machine-detection answer in lieu of an exit-code change).\n\nKeep: exit 0; existing guidance text (print_conflict_guidance rebase.rs:1054-1077); the bn-1abp exec notice (verified working).\nTests: conflicted sync prints WARNING to stderr; sibling-conflict merge summary line; ws sync --format json schema with conflicts.","kind":"bug","labels":["bn-38nz-followup"],"size":"s","title":"Conflicted sync looks like success: add WARNING-grade signal to sync summary and sibling auto-rebase lines"}	blake3:tpRHGInvklgWxsbRk5uNFQ-ZOe8iK7tLZNhaSg0-BRk
1783564921553717	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEypRQ		item.link	bn-38nz	{"link_type":"blocks","target":"bn-mq6j"}	blake3:8zzvxu_BBZvZz70dfyDPYbtRrxJ-thrPFfnnezHiKCc
1783564929161011	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyphQ		item.create	bn-1etl	{"description":"From bn-38nz item 3 (partial — the sidecar-move suggestion is DECLINED, see bn-38nz comments: the in-blob header is load-bearing for the bn-28d1 unforceable tripwire and bn-39i8 sidecar reconstruction).\n\nResidual real sting: a user who hand-resolves the <<<<<<< markers but forgets to delete the \"# structured conflict at ...\" header lines and commits gets blocked at merge by Gate 2 (merge.rs:2842-2862, via find_tool_placeholder_blobs merge.rs:2893-2945 matching TOOL_PLACEHOLDER_PREFIXES materialize.rs:289-290). That's correct — it cannot land on trunk — but the error is tamper-flavored (\"placeholder blob\"), not \"you forgot to delete the header\".\n\nCHANGE: when Gate 2 fires, inspect whether the flagged blob still contains <<<<<<< conflict markers beyond the header. If markers are GONE but the header remains, emit a targeted message: file appears manually resolved but still carries the maw conflict header — delete the leading '# structured conflict...' / '# base blob:' / '# side ... blob:' lines, commit, and re-run merge. Keep the existing tamper-path message when markers are still present. Do not weaken the gate itself (still not bypassable by --force).\nTests: both message variants.","kind":"task","labels":["bn-38nz-followup"],"size":"xs","title":"Gate 2 message: distinguish leftover structured-conflict header from tampered placeholder"}	blake3:UzRgQnaQqoVoEhsfLYvQQB-IOg6ANrrSmHLfAmGGL6U
