1783564944979152	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyqBQ		item.create	bn-nmu7	{"description":"From bn-38nz item 3 (second half). Current --keep both (bn-1nwn) is a per-hunk 3-way merge with gix ConflictResolution::Union = within a genuinely conflicting hunk, both sides concatenated verbatim ours-then-theirs, no dedup (same wrinkle as git merge=union). For the extremely common \"two workers each added a line to the same list\" case (module decls, dep lists, doc bullets) that duplicates shared lines.\n\nCHANGE: add --keep union to ws resolve: like --keep both but with per-hunk line dedup and stable order — preserve ours' hunk-relative order first, then append theirs-only lines in their original relative order; drop lines present in both sides (and lines identical to base already handled by 3-way). gix's driver can't do this (ResolveWithUnion is dumb concat); implement as a post-processing pass in resolve_structured.rs apply_decision (the ThreeWayUnion path, ~lines 611-707) operating on the conflicting regions. Fall back exactly like --keep both for binary/N>2/no-base (BlobReplace/LegacyBlobReplaceWarned paths) — for those, plain concat with the existing legacy warning is fine; do NOT invent whole-file dedup.\n\nMust run the bn-c5ui sanity check (resolve_structured.rs:3321-3372) like other resolutions. Update resolve --help and the conflict guidance text (rebase.rs print_conflict_guidance) to mention --keep union.\nTests: dedup of identical added lines; ours-then-theirs stable order; theirs-only preserved; base-only lines not resurrected; fallback parity with --keep both for AddAdd/binary.","kind":"task","labels":["bn-38nz-followup"],"size":"m","title":"ws resolve --keep union: line-union resolution (dedup + stable order) for conflicted hunks"}	blake3:3DIoGBvvV0sX-50diGrDB7dm6Yo6zz9lRwY5vc3a5nA
