1783566829790177	w-mq6j	itc:v3:AWLJOTPnOZPOUAAAAAAAQdXW-7te6AAAAAEtBQ		item.comment	bn-mq6j	{"body":"DONE in ws bn-mq6j (commit 5bfcc4d4, uncommitted->committed, NOT merged — lead to sync/merge). All 4 items: (1) sync/rebase.rs conflict summaries (new-conflicts, residual-committed, verify-failed) now WARNING-prefixed via new warn_line! macro and duplicated to stderr; residual path list also mirrored to stderr; print_conflict_guidance content unchanged. Pre-flight up-to-date-but-conflicted variant in sync/mod.rs likewise WARNING + stderr. (2) SiblingResult::describe(name) conflicted cases now render 'CONFLICT: rebased with N conflict(s) ... — resolve: maw ws resolve <name> --list'. (3) merge.rs collects conflicted siblings after auto-rebase -> text summary line 'NOTE: N sibling workspace(s) now have conflicts: ...' + new sibling_conflicts field in MergeSuccessOutput JSON (skip-serializing when empty). (4) ws sync --format json (+hidden --json) via OutputFormat::with_json_flag; new SyncJsonOutput {workspace, action(up_to_date|residual_conflicts|rebased|synced|refused_data_loss|cross_target_skip|default_skip|not_found|no_epoch|error), stale, replayed, conflict_count, conflicted_paths, message}; --all --format json emits an array; rebase runs print:false so JSON stdout stays clean; bn-1abp notice still prints (stderr only). Exit code stays 0 for conflicted sync — existing conflict_state_truth tests untouched and green. Tests: tests/sync_loud_conflicts_bn_mq6j_2cvx.rs (10 new integration tests incl. WARNING-on-stderr x3 paths, json schema x3, merge NOTE text+json) + unit tests for describe/json roundtrip. Verification: cargo fmt --check clean; clippy --workspace --all-targets -D warnings clean; full 'just check' via maw exec: EXIT 0, 65/65 'test result: ok', grep of FULL log for FAILED/error/panicked = zero hits."}	blake3:Z3h7USa6o7EYqxCj8KJSxTVuYPIuYZsuth4V4Up3dk4
1783566843716308	w-mq6j	itc:v3:AWLJOTPnOZPOUAAAAAAAQdXW-7te6AAAAAEtBg		item.comment	bn-2cvx	{"body":"DONE in ws bn-mq6j (same commit 5bfcc4d4 as bn-mq6j — shared files, one workspace as directed). Implementation: auto_rebase.rs new compute_overlap_hint() runs BEFORE the rebase mutates the sibling (touched-set only meaningful on old epoch): reuses ff_absorb::compute_ff_changed_paths(old_epoch..new_epoch) x touched::collect_touched_workspace(sibling), intersects; non-empty -> OverlapHint{count(exact), sample_paths(sorted, capped 5)}. Hint attached to all four Rebased* SiblingResult variants; describe() appends '; replayed over commits touching N file(s) this workspace also touches — re-run its tests before merging'. Notice: AutoRebaseNotice gains optional overlap field (serde default + skip-if-none, old notices still parse); write_notice keeps LATEST rebase's hint on merge; render_notice appends the hint + file list, printed on next maw exec (stderr). Best-effort: any failure computing the hint -> None, never blocks the rebase. Tests: integration auto_rebase_overlap_hint_present_when_ranges_overlap (same file touched on different lines -> textually clean rebase + hint in merge output + overlap.count/sample_paths in notice JSON + rendered hint on next exec) and auto_rebase_overlap_hint_absent_when_disjoint (no hint line, no overlap key in JSON); unit tests for suffix rendering, zero-count, notice JSON round-trip. Verification: full 'just check' EXIT 0, 65/65 suites ok, zero FAILED/error in full log; fmt + clippy clean."}	blake3:UTBJqWg-mva_5mC_67hf6VX5hAyoq-5wNT12hXw-QjQ
1783566957351991	w-nmu7	itc:v3:AWKSSTMmfM5MzMQAAAAAQaqtrfbrbYAAAAEyAw		item.comment	bn-nmu7	{"body":"Implementation done in workspace: added --keep union to ws resolve (resolve_structured.rs apply_decision, new ResolveKind::ThreeWayUnionDedup, union_dedup_merge + dedup_conflict_markers post-processing pass operating only on genuinely-conflicting diff3 marker blocks). Fallback for binary/N>2/AddAdd reuses --keep both's legacy blob-concat unchanged. Wired through CLI help text (mod.rs Resolve doc, resolve_structured.rs list/bail hints, rebase.rs print_conflict_guidance). Added 6 integration tests in tests/resolve_keep_union_bn_nmu7.rs (real end-to-end via maw binary: distinct-line union, identical-line dedup, theirs-order preservation, no-resurrection-of-deleted-base-lines, clean-hunk parity with --keep both while conflicting region provably dedups a real gix Union duplicate, AddAdd fallback parity). fmt+clippy clean. Full 'maw exec bn-nmu7 -- just check' running now, will report status next."}	blake3:0I-0F0iOt_4SWSoL367QWc-4V4VwDpGVsn--Eszqn-4
1783567018427609	w-1xmk	itc:v3:AWKZOSSSZJJJkkmcQAAAQbXVVaqrVW4AAAE4BA		item.comment	bn-1xmk	{"body":"DONE (committed 18ebc49c in ws bn-1xmk; NOT merged/pushed). \n\nChanges:\n- crates/maw-cli/src/workspace/working_copy.rs: (1) snapshot_working_copy now returns Err (not Ok(None)) when tree is dirty but stash_create yields no commit — mirrors bn-3mpx, callers abort/repair instead of overwrite (item a). (2) replay_snapshot_with_merge_protection 'overlapping' set broadened via new committed_content_changed() to include any dirty stash path whose committed content changed between anchor and epoch_after — so merge=union journals untouched by any workspace get driver-aware 3-way instead of a bare stash_apply that resolves to the committed side (item b).\n- crates/maw-cli/src/workspace/merge.rs: update_default_workspace captures pre-merge dirty bytes in memory after anchoring; prints 'preserving N uncommitted trunk file(s)'; pins a DURABLE recovery ref refs/manifold/recovery/<ws>/<ts> (pin_recovery_ref_from_oid from the snapshot oid, or pin_pre_merge_recovery_ref building a commit from in-memory bytes when stash failed) — surfaced by 'maw ws recover' as a pinned row (recover.rs already handles pinned refs, no change needed); always routes replay through merge-protection; post-replay verify_trunk_replay_fidelity repairs committed-unchanged files from memory + prints loud recover command on any mismatch (never deletes the durable ref). merge --check gains dirty_trunk_files (informational, never blocking) via list_dirty_trunk_tracked_files.\n- tests/trunk_dirty_preserve_bn_1xmk.rs (4 tests, all green): uncommitted tracked trunk file untouched survives byte-for-byte; union journal untouched-by-workspace keeps uncommitted append (with out-of-maw absorbed commit = the mode-b trigger); dirty-trunk merge pins recovery snapshot visible+searchable in 'maw ws recover' + announces on stderr; merge --check reports dirty trunk files without blocking.\n\nVerification: cargo fmt clean; cargo clippy -p maw-cli --all-targets EXIT 0; targeted suites (merge_gitattributes 44, destroy_recover 63, merge 35, new 28) green; FULL 'maw exec bn-1xmk -- just check' EXIT 0, grepped full 2760-line output: 0 'test result: FAILED', 0 compile errors, 65 'test result: ok'. No refuse-by-default (per lead decision). Left for lead: merge+close."}	blake3:PQ48tz3zhjXEPErPmlC8sTmdhwLjyCkUoyts1dlrVwE
1783567141327867	w-nmu7	itc:v3:AWKSSTMmfM5MzMQAAAAAQaqtrfbrbYAAAAEyBA		item.comment	bn-nmu7	{"body":"DONE — committed 45b740c6 in ws bn-nmu7 (4 files, +731/-39; ws is 1 commit ahead of stale epoch, awaiting lead merge; did NOT sync per lead instruction). IMPLEMENTATION: (1) resolve_structured.rs apply_decision now accepts target==union alongside both — shares every path (ModifyDelete=modifier-only per bn-2pry, per-hunk text guard, bn-c5ui sanity check with size-ratio suppressed, auto-commit/sidecar bookkeeping) but routes text 2-side+base conflicts through new union_dedup_merge(): a Diff3-style merge (clean hunks untouched, byte-identical to --keep both) whose conflicting marker blocks are rewritten in place by dedup_conflict_markers() — ours lines verbatim (incl. internal dups), then theirs-only lines in original order, cross-side dedup only. New ResolveKind::ThreeWayUnionDedup + distinct 'resolved:' summary line. (2) Fallback binary/N>2/AddAdd = exact --keep both legacy blob-concat (warning notes no dedup on fallback). (3) CLI surface: mod.rs Resolve doc-comment + example, resolve_structured module docs, --list 'To resolve' hint (extracted print_resolve_hint to satisfy clippy too_many_lines), keep-empty bail examples, rebase.rs print_conflict_guidance. VERIFICATION: 6 new e2e tests in tests/resolve_keep_union_bn_nmu7.rs, all passing (30/30 in file): distinct additions ours-first; identical added line appears once; theirs-only relative order kept; deleted base line not resurrected; clean hunks byte-parity with --keep both while genuinely-conflicting hunk dedups a real gix-Union duplicate (asserted both=2 occurrences vs union=1 + full expected line vector); AddAdd fallback output identical to --keep both. cargo fmt --check clean; cargo clippy -p maw-cli clean; all 35 existing resolve_structured unit tests green. Full just check: interrupted run logged 63x 'test result: ok', 0 FAILED (incl. DST harness 5/5, contract_drift 4/4); targeted suites re-verified synchronously after."}	blake3:9tZN1TlptXpxCpFPZNmp0DCzsxR2fOOHDzsnB6DtT8o
