1783567910144710	w-1etl	itc:v3:AWKZkkzJJJ_nORAAAAAAQbaraqv93QAAAAExAw		item.comment	bn-1etl	{"body":"Implementation done: maw-core placeholder_blob_has_markers() (materialize.rs) scans a blob for a <<<<<<< line beyond the header; maw-cli merge.rs classify_placeholder_paths() re-reads each Gate-2-flagged blob at workspace HEAD via read_blob_at_path and splits into marker_paths (keeps original tamper message) vs header_only_paths (new targeted 'Delete the leading #header lines...' message). Fails closed on any read error. Shared by ws merge and ws merge --check (same assert_sources_clean_for_merge). resolve.rs/conflict_state.rs left untouched by design: try_reconstruct_sidecar_from_placeholders only parses header lines (stops at first blank line) so a header-only-leftover file already reconstructs successfully there, never hitting a tamper message -- confirmed by re-reading resolve.rs. 4 new tests in tests/gate2_leftover_header_bn_1etl.rs. Running fmt/clippy/targeted tests now, then just check."}	blake3:NWnItI2Rlxx_WA6WdOBFzvoF0dP-0v2c1wrkXRVNFhY
1783568286472453	w-1etl	itc:v3:AWKZkkzJJJ_nORAAAAAAQbaraqv93QAAAAExBA		item.comment	bn-1etl	{"body":"VERIFIED + COMMITTED (a9dcdc32 in ws bn-1etl, not merged/pushed per worker protocol). Evidence: (1) cargo fmt --check clean; (2) cargo clippy -p maw-cli --all-targets -D warnings clean; (3) cargo clippy -p maw-core --all-targets -D warnings clean; (4) new tests 4/4 green (merge_gate2_header_only_leftover_gets_targeted_message, merge_gate2_header_only_leftover_not_bypassable_by_force, merge_check_header_only_leftover_shares_the_targeted_message, merge_gate2_marker_present_keeps_original_tamper_message); (5) existing merge_gate_sidecar.rs 35/35 green (bn-28d1/bn-m6ad/bn-3pgl/bn-3oau invariants intact); (6) full 'maw exec bn-1etl -- just check' exit 0, grepped FULL log (/tmp/bn1etl_just_check.log): 69 'test result:' lines, zero 'test result: FAILED'. Files: crates/maw-core/src/merge/materialize.rs (+placeholder_blob_has_markers), crates/maw-cli/src/workspace/merge.rs (Gate 2 split via classify_placeholder_paths, fails closed on read errors), tests/gate2_leftover_header_bn_1etl.rs (new). resolve --list / conflict_state intentionally unchanged: header-only files there already reconstruct the sidecar from headers and route into the normal structured resolver, no tamper wording on that path. Ready for lead review + merge."}	blake3:kVLHrU8T3_zy9pjkyZsVyLcCuEkUDkLVgEwAp5YglT0
1783568307326062	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyuBQ		item.comment	bn-3eew	{"body":"Implemented in workspace bn-3eew (commit 128b5efe, uncommitted-to-main). CheckResult gained drift_classification: Option<String> (kebab-case slug from epoch_drift::classify_drift, #[serde(default, skip_serializing_if)]), computed read-only in check_merge_result_for_target only when target_updates_epoch (never mutates refs). output_check_result now branches on it: ff-absorbable -> informational 'NOTE: trunk is N commit(s) ahead of the epoch (will be absorbed automatically when you merge).' (no epoch-sync command); ff-blocked -> real WARNING naming the in-flight-workspace-path-overlap reason + points at maw epoch sync / maw doctor --repair; anything else (diverged / classification unavailable) falls back to the original neutral wording. Tests: tests/merge_ff_absorb.rs::check_surfaces_ff_absorbable_trunk_drift_informationally (rewrote the old bn-1huu test, which was actually exercising the FF-absorbable case and had stale scolding-wording assertions) + new check_surfaces_ff_blocked_trunk_drift_as_a_warning; both assert text wording AND the JSON drift_classification field. Verification: cargo fmt --check clean, cargo clippy -p maw-cli --all-targets -D warnings clean, cargo test -p maw-cli --lib (512 passed) + --test merge --test merge_ff_absorb (65+34 passed) all green, maw exec bn-3eew -- just check fully green (grepped whole log for FAILED/error: -- only benign hits: test names and '0 failed' counts)."}	blake3:OYltLQ_108JCc_-nVDmH1J0DVYVuQL3P8yi9Pr2iDsk
1783568313379658	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyuRQ		item.comment	bn-1kop	{"body":"Implemented in workspace bn-3eew (commit 128b5efe, uncommitted-to-main; shared workspace with bn-3eew per task). 1) Text-mode merge success now ends with a stable sentinel: '[OK] merged <ws1>[, <ws2>...] into <branch> @ <12-char-short-sha>' (build_output.candidate short OID), printed after all existing lines, text-mode only (JSON already has MergeSuccessOutput with status:success). 2) ws list --help (workspace/mod.rs List variant doc comment, now #[command(verbatim_doc_comment)]) documents all 8 LifecycleState slugs (missing, conflicted, stale, committed-unintegrated, dirty-uncommitted, abandoned-with-snapshot, clean, integrated) each with a terse meaning/fix-command hint, plus a --format json mention. 3) Verified --format json is already prominently documented in ws merge's help (many examples + per-arg doc); ws list's top-level summary now explicitly mentions it too. Tests: tests/merge.rs::basic_merge_destroy_two_workspaces extended to assert the [OK] sentinel format (workspaces listed, 'into main @', 12-hex-char short sha); new ws_list_help_documents_lifecycle_state_vocabulary_and_json_format (asserts all 8 slugs + --format json in --help) and ws_merge_help_documents_format_json. Verification: cargo fmt --check clean, cargo clippy -p maw-cli --all-targets -D warnings clean, targeted + full lib tests green, maw exec bn-3eew -- just check fully green (grepped for FAILED/error: -- no real failures)."}	blake3:oTiu6bQ9coB11K--GRKI2bS8HtEjm25N14eKu-XjreQ
