1783575385365512	mess-dev	itc:v3:AWKTOcmSTM5M8lAAAAAAQa3darbreoAAAAExAg		item.comment	bn-38nz	{"body":"New footgun found (root cause of repeated 'worker forgot to commit'): agents chain 'maw exec ws -- git add -A && git commit -m ...' — the && splits OUTSIDE maw exec, so git commit runs at the repo root and the workspace silently keeps uncommitted work. Happened to 8 of 9 workers across two waves in mess until prompts mandated two separate maw exec calls. Suggestions: (a) document the && hazard prominently in maw exec --help; (b) add a convenience like 'maw commit <ws> -m ...' (add -A + commit inside the workspace, one atomic command); (c) consider maw exec accepting a quoted compound command via 'sh -c' semantics."}	blake3:QjHFJ7rnygSwnjg35ifhPgNw8KW6WhUDwQMSDvfXs2g
1783614445743205	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyvxQ		item.create	bn-zox8	{"description":"Runner toolchain updated to clippy 1.97 which adds manual_assert_eq (pedantic). Pre-existing assert!(JournalPhase::Start as u8 == 0) at crates/maw-cli/src/migrate/journal.rs:266 now fails the SG1 faithful-clippy workflow (failed on release commit 83742941; passed 13h earlier on older runner). Fix: assert_eq! form. Check for other instances of the pattern repo-wide.","kind":"bug","size":"xs","title":"CI: clippy 1.97 manual_assert_eq trips migrate/journal.rs faithful-clippy gate"}	blake3:AaCAVQZfVvPXWk2fxun8fvJxVAAp5rmjdXnUYYB8248
